Testing on POS: 
Error detection accuracy is significantly improved using proposed approach (after 1000 iterations: 95.1 to 98.6) compared to majority vote and MACE where both had almost similar accuracy (87.4 to 93.9)
using variational inference (VI - AL) gives a substantially higher precision and recall when guiding AL compared to using QBC (difference in precision between 6% to 10% and 10% to 18% in recall)
